The paper deals with compressed sensing and sparse signal recovery, which are core topics in information theory (cs.IT), signal processing (cs.SP), and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the application of compressed sensing to super-resolution problems, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). Finally, the paper proposes a novel algorithm for joint sparse signal recovery and parameter estimation, which can be considered as a sub-topic of statistical inference (cs.SI).
